                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="86316" author="jlevi" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 14:08:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch landed to Master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="85892" author="adilger" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2014 18:49:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Increase priority to critical so that patch will be tracked for landing in 2.6.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="82325" author="jay" created="Wed, 23 Apr 2014 20:23:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch is at: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/10070&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/10070&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="82313" author="jay" created="Wed, 23 Apr 2014 19:10:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The size of cl_page is now 584 bytes. A cl_page is composed of the following sub pages: ccc_page(88 bytes), lov_page(56 bytes), lovsub_page(48 bytes), and osc_page(232 bytes). In osc_page, it has an embedded osc_async_page which is 120 bytes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the short term target is to shrink the cl_page down to below 512 bytes so that it can fit into size-512 slab.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
